<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="cost-vt">cost <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kɒst/    美 /kɔːst/  </p>
<p>(cost, cost)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>价钱为；（使）花费：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>cost (sb) sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Good words cost nothing, but are worth much.
良言不费钱，价值万万千。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The book cost me 15 yuan.
这本书花了我15元。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It will cost you $500 to repair the car.
修理这部汽车要花500美元。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>it costs sth to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It costs a lot to buy all the furniture.
买下所有家具会花很多钱。</p><footer>2015 全国</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>使付出 (代价)；使失去 (生命、健康等)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Such a difficult job costs a lot of time and effort.
这么艰巨的任务要耗费大量的时间和精力。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>cost sb sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The search has cost them a lot of time and money.
搜寻工作已经耗去了他们大量的时间和金钱。</p><footer>人教② – 1</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Careless driving will cost you your life.
开车粗心大意会让你付出生命的代价。</p></div>

<h3 id="cost-spend-pay-take">辨析 cost, spend, pay, take</h3>
<p>这四个词都经常译为“花费”，但用法各不相同。<br />
<strong>cost</strong> 用于“事 / 物 + cost + 人 + 钱数”结构。
<strong>spend</strong> 用于“人 + spend + 时间 + (in) doing / on sth” 结构或“人 + spend + 钱数 + on (doing) sth 结构”。
<strong>pay</strong> 用于“人 + pay + 金钱 + for + 物 ”结构。
<strong>take</strong> 用于“it takes + 人 + 时间 + to do ”结构。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It takes us 3 months to finish the job.
我们花了3个月的时间才完成这个项目。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>costly /'kɒstli/ adj   </p></div>